'''2008年中国南方水灾'''发生在中国的[[中国东部|东部]]及[[中国南部|南部]]，开始于2008年5月，由连日的降雨所导致。[[中国大陆|中国大陆]]受灾的省份包括[[浙江|浙江]]、[[福建|福建]]、[[安徽|安徽]]、[[江西|江西]]、[[湖北|湖北]]、[[湖南|湖南]]、[[广东|广东]]、[[广西|广西]]、[[四川|四川]]、[[重庆|重庆]]、[[贵州|贵州]]、[[云南|云南]]等十二省区受灾。<ref name="scmp1">SCMP. [http://www.scmp.com/portal/site/SCMP/menuitem.2af62ecb329d3d7733492d9253a0a0a0/?vgnextoid=c4dd6946bf78a110VgnVCM100000360a0a0aRCRD&ss=China&s=News  <<''South China Morning Post''>>消息] {{Wayback|url=http://www.scmp.com/portal/site/SCMP/menuitem.2af62ecb329d3d7733492d9253a0a0a0/?vgnextoid=c4dd6946bf78a110VgnVCM100000360a0a0aRCRD&ss=China&s=News |date=20120213074808 }}──" ''Blocked airport highway a black mark for city.'' "    Retrieved on 2008-06-15.</ref> 死亡的人数已达到57人，数百人失踪，<ref>{{Cite web |url=http://www.voanews.com/chinese/w2008-06-16-voa55.cfm |title=美国之音<!-- 机器人生成的标题 --> |accessdate=2011-12-03 |archive-date=2008-06-19 |archive-url=https://web.archive.org/web/20080619204139/http://www.voanews.com/chinese/w2008-06-16-voa55.cfm |dead-url=no }}</ref> 受水灾影响的人口已达2141万人，直接经济损失203亿元。<ref>[[台湾|台湾]][http://1-apple.com.tw/index.cfm?Fuseaction=Article&Sec_ID=3&ShowDate=20080616&IssueID=20080616&art_id=30659366&NewsType=1&SubSec=12 <<苹果日报>>] {{Wayback|url=http://1-apple.com.tw/index.cfm?Fuseaction=Article&Sec_ID=3&ShowDate=20080616&IssueID=20080616&art_id=30659366&NewsType=1&SubSec=12 |date=20080618225512 }} 消息</ref></div></div></div>
== 中国大陆 ==
=== 5月 ===
<!---[[中国日报|中国日报]] reported that torrential rains in the southern provinces killed 64 people in May.<ref name="Chinadaily1">Chinadaily. "[http://www.chinadaily.com.cn/china/2008-06/09/content_6746725.htm Chinadaily]." ''Downpours threaten South China.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-10|2008-06-10]].</ref> According to [[State_Flood_Control_and_Drought_Relief_headquarters|State Flood Control and Drought Relief headquarters]]，floods have claimed 59 lives up to this point of the year.<ref name="hanban">English hanban.edu. "[http://english.hanban.edu.cn/english/China/170283.htm Hanban.edu]." ''South China expects more heavy rain.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-14|2008-06-14]].</ref>--->
=== 6月 ===
<!---From May 28 to June 2, some places in [[广东|广东]] experienced heavy rainfalls. After 7 days, flood situations were investigated by the [[中国气象局|中国气象局]] (CMA) on June 3.<ref>China Meteorological Administration. "[http://www.cma.gov.cn/english/News/t20080605_238451.phtml CMA] {{Wayback|url=http://www.cma.gov.cn/english/News/t20080605_238451.phtml |date=20110716144253 }}." ''Leaders of CMA Pay High Attention on the Flood Situation in Guangdong.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-14|2008-06-14]].</ref> The [[State_Flood_Control_and_Drought_Relief_headquarters|State Flood Control and Drought Relief headquarters]] and [[中央气象台|中央气象台]] (NMC) both raised emergency levels expecting more torrential rain and thunderstorms.<ref name="Chinadaily1" /> On the weekend of June 7-8, [[Guangzhou_Daily|Guangzhou Daily]] reported it to be the heaviest rain storm in 50 years for Guangdong province.<ref name="Yahoo1">Yahoo. "[http://news.yahoo.com/s/nm/20080608/wl_nm/china_weather_dc Yahoo]." ''Worst rainstorms in 50 years hit southeast China.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-14|2008-06-14]].</ref><ref name="Chinadaily1" /> [[梧州|梧州]] was struck with their worst flooding in 100 years.<ref>Standard HK. "[http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=3&art_id=67159&sid=19321761&con_type=1&d_str=20080613&fc=8 Standard HK] {{Wayback|url=http://www.thestandard.com.hk/news_detail.asp?we_cat=3&art_id=67159&sid=19321761&con_type=1&d_str=20080613&fc=8 |date=20110604131804 }}." ''Destructive floods.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-14|2008-06-14]].</ref> In two days the rainfall in some areas measured more than 400 millimetres (15.7 inches).<ref name="Yahoo1" />

On June 14, the [[Ministry_of_Water_Resources_of_the_People's_Republic_of_China|Ministry of Water Resources]] said about 1 million hectares of farmland have been affected with the worst hit provinces being [[Guangdong|Guangdong]]，[[Fujian|Fujian]]，[[Jiangxi|Jiangxi]]，[[Hunan|Hunan]] and [[Hubei|Hubei]].<ref name="hanban" /> From May 25 to June 14, up to 18 people have died, including 2.22 million people were affected in 17 cities in Guangdong. The average rainfall of {{convert|415|mm|in|abbr=on}} was double the long-term level, with the media reporting it as "Freak rain".<ref>Shanghaidaily. "[http://www.shanghaidaily.com/sp/article/2008/200806/20080615/article_363291.htm Shanghaidaily]." ''Freak rainfall lashes nation's south.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-14|2008-06-14]].</ref>

On June 15, more than 300 places in [[Shenzhen|Shenzhen]] were submerged underwater.<ref name="scmp1" /> Floods have forced more than 1.66 million people to evacuate, caused 67,000 houses to collapse, and killed 63 people.<ref>AFP. "[http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5gd0ac134jwO38OJ0QNYTPCf07yyA Agence France-Presse] {{Wayback|url=http://afp.google.com/article/ALeqM5gd0ac134jwO38OJ0QNYTPCf07yyA |date=20080703093320 }}." ''South China ravaged by floods, densely populated north in danger.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-17|2008-06-17]].</ref><ref name="AP"/> Three days later officials in Guangdong warned of a "black june" as [[high_tide|high tide]]s, rain and rivers threatened [[levee|levee]]s. Across the region, 169 were reported killed in the floods.<ref name="Cpost1" />

On June 21, the main precipitation areas include the [[Huaihe_River|Huaihe river]] valleys, [[Guizhou|Guizhou]]，[[Sichuan|Sichuan]] and the middle and lower reaches of the [[Yangtze_River|Yangtze River]]。Heavy rain follow in [[Jiangsu|Jiangsu]]，[[Anhui|Anhui]]，[[Henan|Henan]]，[[Hubei|Hubei]]，[[Chongqing|Chongqing]]，[[Sichuan|Sichuan]]，[[Qinghai|Qinghai]]，and [[Inner_Mongolia|Inner Mongolia]].<ref>Xinhuanet. "[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-06/21/content_8413697.htm Xinhuanet]." ''Heavy rainfall continues in South China.'' Retrieved on [[2008-06-21|2008-06-21]].</ref> At the end of the month, 252 people were killed in the rainstorms and flooding.<ref>Xinhua. "[http://news.xinhuanet.com/english/2008-07/06/content_8496761.htm Xinhuanet]." ''Heavy rainstorms ravage China, leaving at least 12 dead and 3 mln affected.'' Retrieved on [[2008-07-09|2008-07-09]]。--->

